        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5431/12–1545</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Swiss Legation</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Swiss Government is willing to confer immediately with the American
                    Government with a view to controlling, in the year 1946, the importation of
                    Swiss watches and movements by measures which would minimize the indirect
                    importation.</p>
                <p>In order to examine the ways and means to this end, certain data would be
                    desirable, namely: <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>A list of the countries from which indirect delivery of watches to the
                            United States is being made;</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>the names of the firms, in the transit countries as well as in the
                            United States, which handle these indirect deliveries;</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>specification of the watches thus imported, with exact technical
                            description, including make and number;</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                        <item>information on the quantity of, for example, the indirectly imported
                            watches since the beginning of this year.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-15">December 15,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
